<div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:800;color:#5b6b88;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">BIM Uses (aligned to the Owner’s strategic goal)</div>
<div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:14px;background:#ffffff;padding:14px 16px;margin-top:10px;">
<div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:900;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:6px;">Owner’s strategic goal</div>
<div style="color:#1c2430;line-height:1.6;font-size:14px;">“Capture the information required for long-term maintenance and operation of the building, ensuring all assets, systems, and spatial data are accurate and complete.”</div>
</div>
<div style="color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;margin-top:12px;">The BIM Uses table below supports this goal by focusing on coordination, verification, and reliable operational handover.</div>
